A total of 839 deaths were recorded on Tuesday in what was a record figure registered in one day. The country is currently on an adjusted level three lockdown. The new coronavirus strain identified in South Africa appears to be more transmissible than earlier variants. South Africa is the most affected country in terms of Covid-19-related deaths. Due to the curfew, sex workers have moved from their traditional haunts — bars and streets — to houses and on social media. Governors urged to prioritise pending bills and other statutory deductions. Positivity rate has dipped from a high of 20 percent several weeks ago to the current average of 2.8 percent.